WEBVTT

00:02.294 --> 00:05.589
GREAT DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.756 --> 00:10.802
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:10.969 --> 00:14.515
His name: Merlin.

00:29.905 --> 00:31.073
Uncle.

00:31.240 --> 00:33.617
It's late, Arthur. What's troubling you?

00:34.952 --> 00:36.203
Nothing. Nothing at all.

00:37.287 --> 00:40.332
But I've made a decision,
and I felt it only right to inform you right away.

00:40.499 --> 00:42.668
Though I fear you're not gonna like
what I have to say.

00:43.961 --> 00:45.337
I'm going to marry Guinevere.

00:45.754 --> 00:48.006
[SWORD CLATTERS]

00:49.091 --> 00:50.467
Sorry.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.219
That is, if she says yes.

00:52.386 --> 00:53.554
-Sire--
-No.

00:53.720 --> 00:56.848
| know what you're gonna say.
She's a servant, I'm the king.

00:57.015 --> 00:59.685
-It's not the done thing.
-It's a little more serious than that.

00:59.851 --> 01:02.938
ARTHUR: Guinevere has
proved herself valuable support...

01:03.105 --> 01:05.732
...and shrewd counselor
these past few months.

01:05.941 --> 01:09.278
You don't need a woman for support, sire.
I'm your counsel.

01:11.071 --> 01:13.490
| fear you have rather too much stubble
to be my wife.

01:13.699 --> 01:14.741
[CHUCKLES]

01:16.034 --> 01:17.077
[COUGHS]

01:17.244 --> 01:19.538
Good counsel, solid support.
They're exactly what I need.

01:19.705 --> 01:22.749
| don't want a queen who spends her days
floating around the castle...

01:22.916 --> 01:24.334
...agreeing with my every word.

01:24.501 --> 01:27.629
And the people don't want that either.
So I've made up my mind.

01:28.338 --> 01:32.759
| want Guinevere to be my queen,
and I want you to accept her as such.

01:33.427 --> 01:35.012
[CHUCKLES]

01:53.155 --> 01:54.197
My lady.

01:56.783 --> 01:58.952
You better have a good reason
for scaring me like that.

01:59.119 --> 02:00.537
I'm afraid I do.

02:09.880 --> 02:12.924
Arthur is to make Guinevere his queen.

02:14.217 --> 02:16.178
It's just like in my dream.

02:17.179 --> 02:19.431
| will not see that woman upon my throne.

02:19.598 --> 02:22.184
| don't see how we can stop her.

02:26.605 --> 02:28.523
There is one that can ruin
King Arthur's plans.

02:29.566 --> 02:31.902
One that can come between them.

02:32.402 --> 02:36.531
We all have our secrets, and unfortunately
for Guinevere, I know hers.

02:38.200 --> 02:41.411
| know exactly how to destroy her.

03:32.796 --> 03:34.798
[RUSTLING]

03:51.314 --> 03:53.108
| come in peace.

03:59.197 --> 04:01.366
[SNIFFING]

04:03.076 --> 04:06.538
Ah. Morgana Pendragon.

04:07.664 --> 04:10.876
You are destined to bring back the old ways.

04:13.795 --> 04:17.423
| hope to live to see that day.

04:17.591 --> 04:21.595
You are one of the few people
who remember the time of the old religion.

04:23.305 --> 04:25.140
| need your help.

04:29.144 --> 04:33.148
-It was a gift from my sister.
-Ah.

04:33.690 --> 04:37.944
A most interesting present.

04:38.320 --> 04:39.821
Ah.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.115
The price of a soul.

04:44.993 --> 04:48.121
But you do not know how to release it.

04:54.002 --> 04:56.546
| should like to keep it.

05:04.387 --> 05:07.182
Ah. Ah.

05:08.683 --> 05:12.896
The gift is indeed a powerful one...

05:13.063 --> 05:17.400
...but there is only one way
to wield that power.

05:18.777 --> 05:23.156
You must travel
to the last of the five gateways...

05:23.323 --> 05:30.205
...that separate our world
from the world of the dead.

05:32.666 --> 05:36.002
Find the Pool of Nemhain...

05:36.920 --> 05:40.674
...whose waters are as black as night...

05:40.841 --> 05:45.011
...and as still as death itself.

05:46.054 --> 05:51.768
Cast the coin into its depths...

05:51.935 --> 05:54.604
...and your wish will be granted.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.917
My name is Lancelot, my lady.

06:58.585 --> 07:00.879
| am yours to command.

07:16.394 --> 07:18.021
You must be tired.

07:19.022 --> 07:21.942
You've been on a journey
few have ever dreamed of.

07:22.901 --> 07:25.695
| know not where I have been, my lady.

07:26.488 --> 07:28.365
Only that I am yours.

07:30.200 --> 07:31.409
Slow down.

07:31.993 --> 07:33.745
You won't be needing that.

07:34.579 --> 07:36.206
Well, not yet.

07:37.123 --> 07:39.834
We have work to do,
but it's not your sword I require...

07:40.001 --> 07:41.586
...So much as your heart.

07:44.756 --> 07:48.385
There is a woman, a serving girl.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.845
A lowly peasant called Guinevere.

07:53.431 --> 07:55.517
Or Gwen, as she's known to her friends.

07:59.521 --> 08:03.233
There are many that have tried to win
the hand of King Arthur...

08:05.360 --> 08:08.488
...but it was Gwen who won his heart.

08:09.531 --> 08:13.910
She is honest and straightforward,
a simple soul.

08:15.412 --> 08:18.289
Arthur trusts her entirely.

08:21.376 --> 08:23.253
As he does you.

08:24.713 --> 08:26.256
For you are Lancelot...

08:27.007 --> 08:30.468
...the noble, the brave, the honorable.

08:33.763 --> 08:37.058
You're everything
the knights' code stands for.

08:39.894 --> 08:43.398
Before she was Arthur's,
she was yours, Lancelot.

08:43.857 --> 08:46.109
You were her first love.

08:47.986 --> 08:50.405
And you will be her last.

09:18.391 --> 09:19.768
Guinevere...

09:20.351 --> 09:22.896
...will you do me the honor
of becoming my wife?

09:38.870 --> 09:41.915
-Is that a yes?
-Oh, sorry. Yes.

09:42.082 --> 09:43.666
Yes. Yes.

09:43.833 --> 09:45.335
[CHUCKLES]

10:02.227 --> 10:03.353
[DOOR OPENS]

10:03.520 --> 10:05.230
AGRAVAINE:
How is it with our old adversary?

10:06.856 --> 10:08.733
He's learning fast.

10:09.192 --> 10:12.278
Soon he will know enough to convince
everyone he's the Lancelot we all knew.

10:14.614 --> 10:19.077
| thought it would please me,
molding his mind.

10:19.911 --> 10:21.788
Instead, I feel curiously sad.

10:22.497 --> 10:24.833
He was once so mighty.

10:24.999 --> 10:27.127
Now he's nothing but a shade.

10:27.293 --> 10:29.712
| shall be sorry to see him go.

10:32.423 --> 10:34.592
[CHEERING]

10:51.484 --> 10:52.610
I've got to hand it to you.

10:52.777 --> 10:55.530
If nothing else, it's certainly
an original engagement present.

10:56.906 --> 11:00.493
Well, as romantic gestures go,
you could have given her flowers.

11:00.660 --> 11:02.787
Could have had a song written.

11:02.954 --> 11:06.916
Instead, you've given her two days of sweaty
men knocking the sense out of each other.

11:07.083 --> 11:10.670
Exactly as it should be.
My father had a tourney before his wedding.

11:10.837 --> 11:13.756
-It's tradition.
-Ah, so it's not even an original gesture then.

11:13.923 --> 11:15.842
| think my future wife understands.

11:17.468 --> 11:19.179
Thank you very much.

11:24.309 --> 11:26.728
[HORNS PLAYING FANFARE]

11:26.936 --> 11:28.980
[CHEERING]

11:36.362 --> 11:37.530
Who on earth's that?

11:38.323 --> 11:39.616
| have no idea.

11:46.164 --> 11:48.249
[AUDIENCE CHEERS]

12:18.696 --> 12:23.576
| fear I remember very little
after the moment I stepped through the veil.

12:23.743 --> 12:26.955
My story will not be as illuminating
as I would like.

12:27.121 --> 12:28.998
We're just pleased to see you.

12:29.540 --> 12:32.085
Well, pleased and amazed.

12:32.252 --> 12:34.712
| owe everything to the Madhavi people.

12:34.879 --> 12:37.131
When they found me, I was near death.

12:37.548 --> 12:39.509
Luckily for me, their customs dictate...

12:39.676 --> 12:42.512
...that they must give food and shelter
to the needy.

12:42.720 --> 12:43.763
[CHUCKLES]

12:43.930 --> 12:45.181
And I was certainly that.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.100
LEON:
Where did they find you?

12:47.267 --> 12:50.270
On one of the Silk Road passes
high in the Feorre Mountains.

12:50.436 --> 12:51.938
Cenred's kingdom.

12:52.105 --> 12:56.067
| traveled with them for many weeks,
deep into the deserts of the south.

12:57.110 --> 12:59.779
Then slowly, my strengths returned.

12:59.946 --> 13:04.701
When I was able, I earned my passage
the only way I know how: by the sword.

13:04.909 --> 13:06.035
[LEON & PERCIVAL CHUCKLE]

13:07.412 --> 13:10.498
Then I slowly made my way north.

13:10.665 --> 13:11.833
You made your way home.

13:15.795 --> 13:18.673
We can't thank you enough
for what you sacrificed...

13:18.840 --> 13:20.717
...on the Isle of the Blessed.

13:21.718 --> 13:23.303
It will be remembered always.

13:24.137 --> 13:25.346
[SIGHS]

13:25.513 --> 13:27.557
It is indeed good to see you once again.

13:29.183 --> 13:31.102
| would like to propose a toast...

13:31.978 --> 13:34.981
...to the people I hold most dear.

13:35.606 --> 13:36.983
To Camelot.

13:37.900 --> 13:40.820
ALL: To Camelot.
-To Camelot.

13:46.326 --> 13:49.579
-You can have my bed.
-No. No.

13:49.746 --> 13:52.081
Really, after all you've been through...

13:52.832 --> 13:54.083
...It's the least I can do.

13:55.043 --> 13:56.586
Thank you, Merlin.

13:56.753 --> 13:58.671
It's good to see you too.

13:59.464 --> 14:04.302
I've spent so long thinking
about what happened.

14:04.927 --> 14:05.970
Could I have saved you...

14:06.137 --> 14:08.639
...and if there was anything
| could have done.

14:08.848 --> 14:10.516
If I could have used magic.

14:13.561 --> 14:16.230
If any of us had any magic, Merlin...

14:18.191 --> 14:20.902
...then life would be a lot easier.

14:26.824 --> 14:28.368
Good night.

14:29.577 --> 14:31.204
[DOOR CLOSES]

14:36.042 --> 14:37.835
Oh, no.

14:38.002 --> 14:40.505
I've seen that face before.

14:44.008 --> 14:46.761
| want to believe that everything is fine...

14:47.095 --> 14:49.472
...and that we really have Lancelot back.

14:50.890 --> 14:53.184
It certainly looks like him.

14:53.601 --> 14:56.145
-Yeah.
-What is it?

14:59.148 --> 15:00.817
| don't know.

15:02.527 --> 15:04.320
Something's wrong.

15:09.450 --> 15:11.661
When he was telling his story, I sensed it.

15:11.828 --> 15:14.122
The way he greeted me,
that made me suspicious.

15:14.288 --> 15:17.166
But what happened just now,
that's made me sure.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.335
He forgot I had magic.

15:21.212 --> 15:22.922
Lancelot would never do that.

15:25.883 --> 15:29.429
Hmm. Strange indeed.

15:30.680 --> 15:32.223
Give him time.

15:51.492 --> 15:53.453
I'm keen to hear your news.

15:53.619 --> 15:56.372
I'm sure you'll be very proud, my lady.

15:56.539 --> 15:58.499
Arthur and his knights
were completely taken in.

15:59.709 --> 16:04.505
And Gwen? This must be the last thing
she hoped for on the eve of her wedding.

16:04.672 --> 16:07.300
If she was flustered,
she certainly didn't show it.

16:07.967 --> 16:10.845
| fear she truly does love Arthur.

16:11.012 --> 16:12.972
Any feelings she had for Lancelot
are in the past.

16:13.139 --> 16:14.807
| had considered that eventuality.

16:21.856 --> 16:24.400
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

16:30.740 --> 16:33.951
| think it's time to reawaken those feelings.

16:46.214 --> 16:47.798
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

16:57.934 --> 16:59.936
| wasn't sure I'd find you here.

17:00.102 --> 17:02.104
| thought you might
have rooms in the palace.

17:03.564 --> 17:05.900
| want to stay here as long as I can.

17:06.067 --> 17:08.653
It may not be much, but it's my home.

17:09.111 --> 17:10.530
May I come in?

17:12.281 --> 17:14.617
| only want to wish you well.

17:27.672 --> 17:29.924
| never thought I'd see you again.

17:30.091 --> 17:31.342
| know.

17:31.509 --> 17:35.096
-When I heard what you'd done, I felt so guilty.
-No.

17:35.263 --> 17:38.099
You were protecting Arthur,
just as I'd asked.

17:40.268 --> 17:42.603
If it weren't for you, there'd be no wedding.

17:44.522 --> 17:47.108
There are no words to thank you enough.

17:47.275 --> 17:51.028
There is no need for that.
| did what I felt was right in my heart.

17:54.532 --> 17:56.409
You taught me that, Gwen.

17:57.243 --> 17:59.453
To be true to myself.

17:59.954 --> 18:02.164
You will make a wonderful queen.

18:03.332 --> 18:07.503
Your love for your people is surpassed
only by your love for Arthur.

18:14.677 --> 18:19.932
The Madhavi people gave me
this token of good fortune for my journey.

18:22.018 --> 18:26.188
| would like you to wear it,
for I see their goodness in you.

18:29.734 --> 18:31.027
It is a rare thing...

18:32.278 --> 18:35.031
...and I was lucky to have
been touched by it.

18:51.589 --> 18:54.175
| wish you and Arthur
everlasting happiness, Gwen.

19:08.689 --> 19:10.024
[DOOR CLOSES]

19:32.421 --> 19:33.714
[CHEERING]

20:18.050 --> 20:21.303
Mm. The chicken is good.

20:21.470 --> 20:23.097
It's nice broth.

20:23.264 --> 20:25.808
What do you know about necromancy?

20:26.142 --> 20:27.184
What?

20:28.602 --> 20:33.190
Well, you know lots about lots of things,
don't you?

20:33.983 --> 20:38.404
Necromancy is the most dangerous
of all magical practices.

20:38.571 --> 20:40.281
Even in the days of the old religion...

20:40.448 --> 20:44.160
...such sorcery was viewed
with the utmost suspicion.

20:46.328 --> 20:49.457
| know I'm going to regret
asking this, Merlin...

20:50.416 --> 20:52.668
...but why do you want to know?

20:58.257 --> 21:00.426
| think that someone
has raised Lancelot from the dead.

21:02.845 --> 21:05.139
By "someone,â€
| presume you mean Morgana?

21:05.723 --> 21:07.016
Yeah.

21:08.100 --> 21:11.562
The old legends do speak of such creatures.

21:11.729 --> 21:13.606
They call them shades.

21:14.440 --> 21:16.776
Poor, tormented souls
summoned from their rest...

21:16.942 --> 21:18.694
...by the necromancer's art.

21:19.403 --> 21:20.696
So it is possible?

21:23.324 --> 21:26.952
Even if it is possible,
we have no way of knowing for sure.

21:32.541 --> 21:34.668
Or do we?

21:51.310 --> 21:53.354
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

21:58.526 --> 22:00.194
[THUD NEARBY]

22:10.371 --> 22:11.956
It's time.

22:39.859 --> 22:41.944
| didn't want it to be true.

22:43.028 --> 22:45.865
| know. We all wanted him back.

22:46.031 --> 22:47.324
Yeah.

22:47.783 --> 22:49.493
More than anything.

22:50.536 --> 22:56.959
This man's a shadow of his former self,
a shadow with ill intent.

22:57.126 --> 22:59.253
Do you think he means to harm Arthur?

22:59.420 --> 23:03.132
Whatever his reason for being here,
it can't be good.

23:09.054 --> 23:10.973
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

23:21.066 --> 23:22.484
Here.

23:23.694 --> 23:25.237
Let me.

23:26.989 --> 23:28.616
Thank you.

23:30.951 --> 23:33.871
| just wanted to wish you well.

23:36.498 --> 23:39.543
Shouldn't you be saying that
to your future husband?

23:39.710 --> 23:41.420
| do.

23:42.338 --> 23:44.048
| have.

23:46.133 --> 23:47.801
| will.

23:51.263 --> 23:53.807
I'm sorry. I don't know why I'm here.

24:07.947 --> 24:09.823
[WHINNYING]

24:24.046 --> 24:25.798
[CHEERING]

25:12.052 --> 25:13.762
[GASPING]

25:15.139 --> 25:16.557
[CHEERING]

25:29.069 --> 25:31.780
Don't look so worried, Merlin. Arthur won.

25:32.239 --> 25:33.574
Yeah.

25:35.034 --> 25:37.536
Now he's in the final with Lancelot.

25:37.703 --> 25:39.121
Yeah, I know.

25:39.288 --> 25:41.457
People are gonna love that.

25:45.210 --> 25:47.129
[AUDIENCE CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

26:06.523 --> 26:09.902
You must be ready, Merlin.
Your magic might be needed.

26:42.601 --> 26:45.646
Arthur should withdraw.
He's in no fit state to continue.

26:46.063 --> 26:48.482
He wouldn't withdraw if his head
was hanging by a thread.

27:25.435 --> 27:27.062
What's going on? Why did he yield?

27:59.845 --> 28:01.972
| suppose I should be pleased.
Arthur's alive.

28:10.689 --> 28:11.732
My liege.

28:11.899 --> 28:14.693
Arise, Sir Lancelot. That's not necessary.

28:17.070 --> 28:20.157
| always thought you were the noblest
of my knights. You just proved me right.

28:21.408 --> 28:22.659
Thank you for your courtesy.

28:25.078 --> 28:26.371
It won't be forgotten.

28:38.550 --> 28:39.593
Your Highness.

28:45.307 --> 28:48.352
If he's not here to kill Arthur,
what's he here for?

28:51.313 --> 28:52.689
| don't know.

28:58.654 --> 29:00.155
| wish I did.

29:27.724 --> 29:29.685
[FOOTSTEPS]

29:56.086 --> 29:57.504
Everything is prepared.

29:57.671 --> 30:00.590
Gwen is on her way to our assignation
as we speak.

30:00.757 --> 30:03.760
AGRAVAINE: You've done well. The Lady
Morgana will be very pleased with you.

31:03.945 --> 31:05.280
Arthur.

31:07.616 --> 31:09.159
Arthur.

31:09.534 --> 31:12.412
I'm sorry. There's something you must see.

31:19.294 --> 31:21.296
[SWORD UNSHEATHES]

31:37.562 --> 31:39.606
Are you sure this is safe?

31:40.023 --> 31:44.027
No one visits the council chambers
at this hour of the night.

31:53.370 --> 31:55.038
[GROANS]

32:26.403 --> 32:28.238
[ARTHUR YELLING]

32:51.344 --> 32:52.512
Please!

32:58.852 --> 33:00.187
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

33:03.773 --> 33:05.025
[YELLING]

33:05.233 --> 33:08.904
No, please! Please. Please. Stop, please.

33:09.070 --> 33:10.947
Please, this has to stop. Please!

33:11.573 --> 33:14.951
Please. Stop. This has to stop, please.

33:44.606 --> 33:45.649
[SOBBING]

33:45.815 --> 33:48.568
AGRAVAINE: Far be it for me to advise you
on personal matters, sire...

33:48.735 --> 33:51.488
...but this is also a matter of state.

33:51.863 --> 33:56.409
You've been made a fool of,
and you must respond robustly.

33:57.327 --> 33:59.621
Of course, in the days of your father...

33:59.788 --> 34:03.250
...adultery in noble families
was punishable by death.

34:04.084 --> 34:08.380
And as for Lancelot,
death's too good for him.

34:08.547 --> 34:10.966
He must die, but...

34:12.425 --> 34:13.467
...painfully.

34:22.851 --> 34:24.563
[DOOR OPENS]

34:41.288 --> 34:42.746
ARTHUR:
You will leave, please.

34:49.087 --> 34:50.797
All of you.

34:51.464 --> 34:52.507
Now.

35:02.892 --> 35:04.144
You too, uncle.

35:05.520 --> 35:07.856
-Sire--
-Now.

35:38.678 --> 35:41.681
What are you still doing on your knees?
Am I just your king?

35:41.848 --> 35:43.642
Get up, for goodness' sake.

35:44.976 --> 35:46.770
| was to be your husband.

36:05.455 --> 36:06.706
What happened, Guinevere?

36:11.836 --> 36:15.006
We were happy. I know we were happy.

36:18.343 --> 36:19.469
You felt it too?

36:24.891 --> 36:27.185
-But you love him? You've always loved him?
-No.

36:27.352 --> 36:29.396
All those times you said
you wanted to be with me.

36:29.562 --> 36:31.189
| meant every word.

36:31.356 --> 36:34.943
Tomorrow was our wedding day.

36:37.696 --> 36:38.988
| know.

36:39.155 --> 36:41.783
-If you had worries--
- I wasn't worried.

36:41.950 --> 36:44.744
-If you had doubts--
- I didn't have any doubts.

36:44.911 --> 36:47.664
Then forgive me,
because I must be really stupid!

36:47.831 --> 36:49.416
What were you doing?

36:49.624 --> 36:51.209
[WHIMPERS]

36:53.002 --> 36:56.631
-Sorry.
-No. No.

36:56.798 --> 36:58.883
No, it is I who should be sorry.

37:02.887 --> 37:05.181
You mean everything to me, Arthur.

37:07.308 --> 37:11.354
Once, there was Lancelot, a long time ago.

37:11.521 --> 37:15.066
But I haven't considered him in that way
for many years.

37:16.109 --> 37:19.821
| thought he was dead.
| thought I would never see him again.

37:20.530 --> 37:24.868
And then when I did, I was overwhelmed.

37:25.034 --> 37:27.704
| was drawn to him. I couldn't stop myself.

37:27.871 --> 37:30.039
| don't know why.

37:30.206 --> 37:35.253
| love you. You mean everything to me.

37:36.963 --> 37:40.467
All these years, I've waited for you.

37:40.633 --> 37:43.553
You only had to wait one more day.

37:47.932 --> 37:51.686
All I've ever wanted is to be your queen.

37:52.729 --> 37:54.606
| still want to be your queen.

37:56.232 --> 37:57.984
Do you know what they're saying?

38:01.946 --> 38:04.115
That in my father's day,
you'd be put to death.

38:16.586 --> 38:18.505
| don't want to see you dead, Guinevere...

38:22.258 --> 38:24.552
...but I don't want to see you.

38:26.346 --> 38:29.098
| cannot look on you every day.

38:29.265 --> 38:31.559
-You will leave Camelot at first light.
-Arthur--

38:31.726 --> 38:33.937
You return upon pain of death.

38:35.814 --> 38:39.609
No. No, no, no. I cannot be without you.

38:39.776 --> 38:42.028
That is my decision.

38:43.530 --> 38:45.615
Where will I go?

38:55.458 --> 38:56.751
| am sorry.

38:59.128 --> 39:01.714
| am truly sorry.

39:04.342 --> 39:05.927
[DOOR CLOSES]

39:13.017 --> 39:16.062
This is what Morgana wanted all along.

39:16.229 --> 39:20.483
She couldn't suffer the ignominy
of seeing Gwen on her throne.

39:20.650 --> 39:23.194
It is indeed a cruel revenge.

39:23.361 --> 39:25.947
But it is Morgana who created it.

39:27.323 --> 39:29.701
| must make Arthur see that.

39:29.868 --> 39:31.661
If he knew that Lancelot was a shade--

39:31.828 --> 39:34.581
It wouldn't change what Gwen has done.

39:34.747 --> 39:38.126
It is her betrayal that matters to the king,
Merlin.

39:38.293 --> 39:40.753
Telling him of Lancelot's true nature
won't change that.

39:43.923 --> 39:46.718
It's Gwen who must pay the price.

40:08.364 --> 40:09.949
This is from our Lady Morgana.

40:12.493 --> 40:14.412
She has one last wish for you.

40:16.039 --> 40:18.625
Whatever my lady desires.

40:18.917 --> 40:19.959
I'm hers to command.

41:25.358 --> 41:27.402
It's not too late, sire.

41:31.030 --> 41:35.451
| know what Gwen did was desperately wrong,
but she is a good person.

41:35.618 --> 41:37.662
| truly believe that.

41:40.373 --> 41:42.250
As do |, Merlin.

41:45.378 --> 41:49.132
-As do I.
-Can you find it in your heart to forgive her?

41:52.093 --> 41:53.177
That's not the problem.

41:55.179 --> 41:56.764
Agravaine?

41:59.809 --> 42:02.061
Well, it is Agravaine, isn't it?

42:03.271 --> 42:06.482
He's wrong.
The people won't find you weak or a fool.

42:06.649 --> 42:10.069
They will find you merciful, understanding.

42:14.449 --> 42:17.118
You're brave to speak out, Merlin.

42:17.618 --> 42:19.912
Gwen's your friend. I understand.

42:20.079 --> 42:21.748
I'm afraid you're wrong.

42:24.542 --> 42:27.003
| love Gwen with all my heart.

42:27.670 --> 42:30.965
I'm sure, in time, I'll find a way to forgive her.

42:32.550 --> 42:34.343
But I'll never trust her.

42:35.887 --> 42:39.724
| can't live like that.
Not as a king and certainly not as a husband.

42:40.391 --> 42:42.935
And though it pains me...

42:44.187 --> 42:45.938
...it's best that she's gone.

42:50.151 --> 42:51.736
AGRAVAINE:
Sire.

42:55.823 --> 42:57.909
The guards found him.

43:00.703 --> 43:02.371
What happened?

43:03.414 --> 43:05.416
It appears he took his own life.

43:05.583 --> 43:07.794
ARTHUR:
| guess we shouldn't be surprised.

43:10.379 --> 43:12.048
In all ways but one...

43:12.965 --> 43:14.842
...Lancelot was a man of honor.

43:18.179 --> 43:20.640
See to it that he receives a proper burial.

43:50.002 --> 43:53.339
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

43:55.967 --> 43:57.635
[INHALES]

44:05.893 --> 44:07.019
Merlin.

44:09.814 --> 44:11.357
Thank you.

45:09.290 --> 45:10.958
MALE VOICE:
Merlin.

45:11.167 --> 45:12.460
GAIUS:
You were right to be wary.

45:12.627 --> 45:15.504
The druids build shrines
to bring rest to tormented souls.

45:15.671 --> 45:17.048
[BIRD SCREAMS]

45:17.256 --> 45:18.966
No! No!

45:20.051 --> 45:21.636
What the hell do you think you're doing?

45:21.844 --> 45:24.597
Elyan may have disturbed
the spirit at the shrine.

45:29.268 --> 45:31.020
MERLIN:
Arthur!

46:16.107 --> 46:17.108
[English - US - SDH]
